-- Hanover Compressor, Universal Compression agree to merge
-- 
-- Mon Feb 5, 2007 6:44am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/05/us-hanover-universalcompression-idUSWNAS959420070205

 

 (Reuters) - Oil and gas equipment maker Hanover Compressor Co. HC.N and Universal Compression Holdings Inc. UCO.N, a provider of natural gas compression products, agreed to merge, the companies said. 


 On a stock-for-stock deal, Hanover stockholders will get 0.325 shares of the new company for each share held and Universal shareholders will get 1.0 share of the new company for each share they own, the companies said in a statement. Hanover stockholders will initially own about 53 percent of the new company and Universal stockholders will hold about 47 percent. The merger is expected to be tax free to stockholders of both companies. (Reporting by Hari Kumar in Bangalore)